# RDS = Managed Database Service
ğŸ¢ AWS handles: Backups, updates, security
ğŸ‘¨ğŸ’» You handle: Your data and queries

RDS vs Your Own Database:
text

YOUR OWN DATABASE:
âŒ Handle backups
âŒ Apply security patches  
âŒ Monitor performance
âŒ Scale manually

AWS RDS:
âœ… Automated backups
âœ… Automatic updates
âœ… Built-in security
âœ… Easy scaling

Creating RDS Database:
bash

1. AWS Console â†’ RDS â†’ Create database
2. Choose: PostgreSQL
3. Template: Free tier
4. Settings: 
   - DB name: studentdb
   - Username: postgres  
   - Password: yourpassword
5. Public access: Yes (for learning)
6. Create database
7. Wait 10-15 minutes

ğŸ¬ 359. Deploying App on Beanstalk (4min)
