ğŸ¬ 363. Running the Task for Postgres (4min)
Database in ECS:
bash

# Two Options:
OPTION 1: Use RDS (Recommended)
- Managed PostgreSQL
- Better for production

OPTION 2: PostgreSQL in ECS  
- PostgreSQL in Docker container
- Good for development

PostgreSQL Task Definition:
json

{
  "family": "postgres-task",
  "containerDefinitions": [{
    "name": "postgres",
    "image": "postgres:15",
    "portMappings": [{
      "containerPort": 5432,
      "hostPort": 5432
    }]
  }]
}

ğŸ¬ 364. Pushing Docker Image to ECR (4min)
What is ECR?
bash

# ECR = Elastic Container Registry
ğŸ“¦ Stores Docker images
ğŸ” Private and secure
âš¡ Fast deployments

Process:
bash

1. Build Docker image locally
2. Tag image: docker tag my-app:latest account.dkr.ecr.region.amazonaws.com/my-app:latest
3. Login to ECR: aws ecr get-login-password
4. Push image: docker push account.dkr.ecr.region.amazonaws.com/my-app:latest

